<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-12-24T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-12-24T10:00:00-05:00" n="361" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d361">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Germany)/12–2447:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Political Adviser for Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MRD1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Murphy</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-12-24T16:00:00+01:00">December
                                    24, 1947—4 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>3786. Personal for <persName corresp="#p_GW1">Gallman</persName>. There
                            seems to be surprising discrepancy between the viewpoint attributed to
                                <persName corresp="#p_KSIA1">Kirkpatrick</persName><note n="3" xml:id="d361fn1">See telegram 6607, December 23, from London, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note> and our understanding of Mr.
                                <persName corresp="#p_BE1">Bevin</persName>’s views, particularly
                                <persName corresp="#p_KSIA1">Kirkpatrick</persName>’s opinion that
                            central government should be established promptly, presumably at
                            Frankfurt.</p>
                        <p>On subject of payment of reparations to the Soviet Union, we, of course,
                            do not agree with <persName corresp="#p_KSIA1">Kirkpatrick</persName>’s
                            view that the Russians should be appeased in order to obtain respect for
                            the Four-Power agreement which authorizes the powers to occupy sectors
                            in the greater Berlin area.</p>
                        <p>Sent Department 3786, to Moscow as 598, for London as 464.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_MRD1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Murphy</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>